Sentencas: A new capability has been developed for analyzing solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Lattice expansion of LSCF-6428 cathodes measured by in situ XRD during SOFC operation

Sentencas: This paper describes the initial results of in situ X-ray diffraction (XRD) of the cathode on an operating anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Lattice expansion of LSCF-6428 cathodes measured by in situ XRD during SOFC operation

Sentencas: It has been demonstrated that XRD measurements of the cathode can be performed simultaneously with electrochemical measurements of cell performance or electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS).
Titulo: Lattice expansion of LSCF-6428 cathodes measured by in situ XRD during SOFC operation

Sentencas: While improvements to the technique are still to be made, the XRD pattern of a lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) cathode with the composition La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF-6428) was found to continually but gradually change over the course of more than 60 h of operation in air under typical SOFC operating conditions.
Titulo: Lattice expansion of LSCF-6428 cathodes measured by in situ XRD during SOFC operation

Sentencas: It was determined that the most significant change was a gradual increase in the cubic lattice parameters of the LSCF from 3.92502 angstrom (as determined from the integration of the first 20 h of XRD patterns) to 3.92650 angstrom (from the integration of the last 20 h).
Titulo: Lattice expansion of LSCF-6428 cathodes measured by in situ XRD during SOFC operation

Sentencas: This analysis also revealed that there were several peaks from unidentified minor phases that increased in intensity over this timeframe.
Titulo: Lattice expansion of LSCF-6428 cathodes measured by in situ XRD during SOFC operation

Sentencas: After a temporary loss of airflow early in the test, the cell generated between 225 and 250 mW cm(-2) for the remainder of the test.
Titulo: Lattice expansion of LSCF-6428 cathodes measured by in situ XRD during SOFC operation

Sentencas: A large low frequency arc in the impedance spectra suggests the cell performance was gas diffusion limited and that there is room for improvement in air delivery to the cell.
Titulo: Lattice expansion of LSCF-6428 cathodes measured by in situ XRD during SOFC operation
